        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 10:24AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 1024 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Freeland, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bay City, Auburn, Freeland, Kawkawlin, Essexville, Laporte, Hemlock,
Bay City State Recreation Area, and Shields.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
